# Application Layer

- Put application code under `<feature>/application`.
- Application services orchestrate feature use cases and transactions.
- Name application services `<Domain>Service`, for example `UserService`.
- Put DTOs, models, and value objects under `<feature>/domain`, not application.
- Application services may depend on domain models and the feature's infrastructure `JpaRepository`.
- Validate business constraints before calling the repository.
- Application services map saved entities to response DTOs before returning to controllers.
- Never return JPA entities from an application service to the web layer.
- Do not put HTTP, servlet, controller, or JPA entity mapping logic in this layer.
- Keep business invariants in domain objects when they naturally belong to an aggregate.
- Mark transaction boundaries on application service methods.
